Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Seal impression
Description: Small impression of a seal of the scaraboïde type applied on a bond. One can see two faced cobras, separated by the name of the goddess Hathor and surmounted by a nefer sign ("beautiful, good, perfect"). The edge of a second print is visible at the top.
